    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1822"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1822">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.1123L25/18.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 189.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your Nos. 607 and 614
                    of the 8th and 14th ultimo, relating to the indifference shown by the Panaman
                    authorities to taking any effective steps to redress the wrongs committed in the
                    riots of February 14 last in Panama and on April 2 last in Colon.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your note of September 4 last to the Panaman Foreign
                    Office in reply to its note on the subject and will await the receipt of a
                    response from the Foreign Office to it before giving instructions in the
                    matter.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
